OL,3,GUK long range forecast
OL,4,
OL,5,COutlook for Wed 1 Apr to Fri 10 Apr
OL,6,FHigh pressure to the southwest of the
OL,7,FUK, with weather fronts rounding the
OL,8,Fhigh to affect northern parts at
OL,9,Ftimes, is likely the dominant pattern
OL,10,Fthrough this period. Wetter and
OL,11,Fwindier weather can be expected in the
OL,12,Fnorth, while further south, drier and
OL,13,Fmore settled conditions are more
OL,14,Flikely. There is a chance of deeper
OL,15,Flows moving across the UK at times,
OL,16,Fbringing wetter and windier weather
OL,17,Fmore widely. Later in the period, high
OL,18,Fpressure may spread across much of the
OL,19,FUK leading to more widespread settled
OL,20,Fconditions. Whilst temperatures will
OL,21,Fbe generally near to or a little above
OL,22,Faverage, some colder interludes are
OL,23,QppppppppppppppppppppGSource: Met Office
OL,23,Fpossible, especially in the north,
OL,24,ANext Page  BWeather  CReg News  FReg TV
OL,24,Fwhere there could be some wintry
OL,25,Fshowers at times.
FL,164,160,301,260,100,100
